column4: hi, I can't lauch update manager... i'm using jaunty 9.04, want to upgrade to 9.10 but I just can't... I tried sudo apt-get dist-upgrade but nothing happened from terminal
go into synaptic and check which repository it's pointing to, you might want to try another one

open a terminal and type upd
open a terminal and typ

it says here ubuntu-desktop is the newest version
can you try an apt-get install python-gtk2?
